Patch Set 13:

I tried 19368 with the test case from 16374 and it worked with a small change that enables 4 MiB I/O without scripting additional ofd settings:

@@ -2751,7 +2751,7 @@ static int ofd_init0(const struct lu_env *env, struct ofd_device *m,
        ofd_slc_set(m);
        m->ofd_grant_compat_disable = 0;
        m->ofd_soft_sync_limit = OFD_SOFT_SYNC_LIMIT_DEFAULT;
-       m->ofd_brw_size = ONE_MB_BRW_SIZE;
+       m->ofd_brw_size = PTLRPC_MAX_BRW_SIZE;

        /* statfs data */
        spin_lock_init(&m->ofd_osfs_lock);

I took a quick look at the code and it seems like st_blksize does not depend on the file, its striping and corresponding max_pages_per_rpc. Does it make sense to make it like in 16374?

So, 19368 is ok with me if a test case is added from 16374 or a similar one is added to 19368.
